note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Canticles (from a Psalter) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 3-line initial "D" is in red with blue flourishes; 1-line initials are in red square capitals; rubrics written in red rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus and punctus versus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Psalter (Gallican) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Psalter (Gallican) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the Psalms are written according to verse lines; 3-line initial "N" at the beginning of Psalm 36 is a square capital in orange; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses are in orange; rubrics written in orange rustic capitals; the first line of Psalm 36 is written in brown capitals with uncial and rustic capital forms; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; a contemporary hand has written "...viam" with neumes in the margin of fol. 2r.

title: Psalter (Gallican) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Psalter (Gallican) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the Psalm is written according to verse lines; 8-line initial "D" is in red outline and is filled with blue and green wash; the style is reminiscent of Regensburg decoration; the letters of the first two words of the Psalm are written on four lines to the right of the initial in 1-line square capitals that alternate between red and blue highlighted with red; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses are written in red square capitals; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; line fillers and line dividers in red.

title: Psalter (Gallican) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Psalter (Gallican) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 3-line initials at the beginning of Psalms are in red, which in places has oxidized to a silver color; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses are in red square capitals; rubrics written in red rustic capitals; the first line of each Psalm is written in brown rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials at the beginning of each Mass are in red square capitals; 1-line initials are in red square capitals; rubrics written in red rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: three lines of a large initial "F" (?) that is half green and half red are preserved on fol. 1r; 1-line initials at the beginning of prayers are in red square capitals; smaller 1-line initials are in brown rustic capitals highlighted with red; rubrics are written in a mixture of red capitals and minuscule forms; liturgical directions are written in brown minuscule with some rustic capital forms and are dotted with red; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Homiliary (of Paul the Deacon?) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Homiliary (of Paul the Deacon?) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are written in brown rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation in the same ink as the text.

title: Decretales (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Decretales (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line capital "A" is a red square capital; 1-line initials are in brown capitals; the rubric is written in red minuscule; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Aeneid (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Aeneid (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: a portion of the initial "P" of Book 3 is preserved, written in red; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses are in brown in a mixture of rustic capital and uncial forms; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Historia monarchorum (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Historia monarchorum (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials at the beginning of chapters are in red uncials; other 1-line initials are in brown, once filled with red, and are a mixture of uncial, rustic capital, and enlarged minuscule forms; rubrics are written in red rustic capitals; a line divider is in brown filled with red; punctuated with the puncus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Verba Seniorum (Vitae Patrum) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in rounded early gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Verba Seniorum (Vitae Patrum) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2- and 3-line initials are in red with red and blue penwork; 1-line initials are in brown uncials; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and colon; accents and hyphenation in the same ink as the text.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: initials of antiphons and responses are 1-line red capitals; 1-line initials for verses and Psalm incipits are in brown highlighted with red; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation in the same ink as the text; interlinear neumes in the St. Gall style, somewhat surprising in a manuscript of this date; differentiae in roman numerals with neumes in the St. Gall style are in the outer margins for antiphons with full text.

title: Commentary on Ps.-Gilbert of Poitiers, Lib. VI principiorum (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a small gothic script with frequent abbreviations (scriptura notularis).

title: Commentary on Ps.-Gilbert of Poitiers, Lib. VI principiorum (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: spaces are left for two 2-line initials, but they have not been added; 1-line initials are in brown capitals; quotations from the text are underlined in brown; paragraph marks are in brown; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Bible, Leviticus (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Bible, Leviticus (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: spaces are left within the text for 1-line initials but they have not been added; other 1-line initials are in brown; punctuated with the punctus, though it is extremely rare; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Bible, Kings and Wisdom (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Bible, Kings and Wisdom (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials of each verse are in brown highlighted with red; punctuated with the punctus and the punctus elevatus.

title: Gospel Harmony, Matthew and Luke (with commentary) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in early gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Gospel Harmony, Matthew and Luke (with commentary) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: each section from the Bible begins with a 2-line initial in red; the corresponding sections of the commentary begin with a 1-line red initial; other 1-line initials in both the text and the commentary are in black; the lemmata in the commentary are underlined with red; canon table numbers are written in black in the margins and are surrounded by red boxes; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Bible, Commentary on Wisdom (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a small gothic script with frequent abbreviations (littera textualis currens).

title: Bible, Commentary on Wisdom (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are in black; punctuated with the punctus; quotations from Wisdom are underlined in black.

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2- and 3-line initials at the beginning of lessons are in red uncials; the initials for prayers are in red and are 3-line initials when they occur at the beginning of a line and 1-line initials when they occur within a line; 1-line initials within lessons are in black; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the initials of the lessons are slightly enlarged; they alternate blue with red penwork or red with blue penwork; initials at the beginning of verses are highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; liturgical directions are written in black and are underlined in red; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Calendar and Computus (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Calendar and Computus (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: on fol. 1 columns 3 and 4 are written in red, as is the slightly enlarged "A" indicating a Sunday on every seventh line in column 2; the enlarged abbreviations for the words "kalendae", "nonae", and "idus" are also red; the script in the columns of the computus tables alternates black and red; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Liber Constitutionem Sororum O.P. (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Liber Constitutionem Sororum O.P. (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 3-line initials at the beginning of chapters are in red with red ornamentation; 1-line initials in the capitula list are in red; other 1-line initials are in black highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; paragraph marks in red are occasionally used in the margins to mark the beginning of a new lesson; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus.

title: Lectionary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Lectionary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: one 4-line and two 3-line initials are in red, decorated with blue penwork; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses are in brown uncials highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation and accents in the same ink as the text; there are three signs that occur over syllables of words, one similar to a backwards "3", one similar to a squarish backwards "C", and the third a virgule; perhaps theese are pitch or accent marks or some other type of aid for reading aloud.

title: Decretales (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Decretales (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: there are guide letters for initials at the beginning of each capitulum, but the initials have not been added; 1-line initials are in red; the heading of titulus VI is written in red; punctuated with the punctus; paragraph marks are in red ink, brackets in brown; corrections have been made by several contemporary hands.

title: Sermon 69 (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in early gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Sermon 69 (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are in brown highlighted with red; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Copy of a Judicial Decision (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in notarial script by the notary Johannes, son of Julianus.

title: Copy of a Judicial Decision (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: The document begins with a flourished initial "I"; 1-line initials are in brown; the notary's sign is in the center of the lower margin; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Liber Poenitentiarius (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a rounded gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Liber Poenitentiarius (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: there are spaces with guide letters for 2-line initials, but they have not been added; rubrics in red in the same script as the text; guides for the rubricator are in the margins in light brown ink; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Digesta (fragment).
note_text: Script: text of the Digest in a rounded gothic script (littera textualis), that of the commentary in a smaller hand (notularis), perhaps later.

title: Digesta (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: initials of the names of authorities alternate 1- and 2-line red and blue capitals; the first word of each section begins with a 1-line capital alternating red and blue; guide letters for both initials are written in light brown ink; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Digesta (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a rounded gothic script (littera textualis); later marginal and interlinear notes.

title: Digesta (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: initials of the names of authorities are 2- and 3-line blue capitals with red penwork; the initials of the first word of each section are 1-line red capitals; 1-line initials within the text are in black; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; paragraph marks are either red, blue, or black; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Prayers (in Latin and Middle High German) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Prayers (in Latin and Middle High German) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are in black capitals highlighted with red; sections within the Rhymica oratio are marked by paragraph marks in red; rubrics in the prayers are written in black minuscule and underlined in red; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Digesta with glossa ordinaria of Accursius (fragment)
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis), with a larger script for the text and a smaller script for the commentary (notularis), possibly by a different hand; later marginal and interlinear notes in a cursive hand.

title: Digesta with glossa ordinaria of Accursius (fragment)
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are enlarged minuscule forms, preceded by a paragraph mark in blue; running chapter number "II" in the upper center of both sides is red and blue; punctuated with the punctus, though rarely.

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in early gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials at the beginning of each Mass and 1-line initials for other prayers are in red; rubrics are written in in red in the same script as the text, with occasional use of uncial or rustic capital forms; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Sermons (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in an informal gothic script (approaching a littera textualis currens).

title: Sermons (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: spaces have been left at the beginning of homilies for 2-line initials, but they have not been added; 1-line initials are in brown; punctuated with the punctus; a contemporary hand has made some corrections to the text in a darker ink.

title: Judicial Decision (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in notarial script by Rolandinus.

title: Judicial Decision (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: at the opening of the document there is a design in brown ink resembling a chalice; a cross stands above the entire document; the initial "E" of the notary's signature is a 2-line square-shaped capital in black ink decorated with dots; punctuated with the punctus and, at the end of the document, the punctus versus.

title: Duties of the Cellarer of the Church of St. Victor, Xanten (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in an early gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Duties of the Cellarer of the Church of St. Victor, Xanten (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are in black, highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus, some of which are in red.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written by three scribes in gothic script (littera textualis); one scribed copied fol. 1, another copied fol. 2r, and a third copies fol. 2v.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials at the beginning of the antiphon on fol. 1 are in red; the guide letters for these initials are still visible in light brown ink and some have been ornamented, including one with a crude figure of a person; 2-line initials at the beginning of verses on fol. 1 are in black with black penwork; fol. 2v begins with a very crude 2-line round D in red; rubrics written in red; musical notation is in black and on fol. 1 is on a 4-line staff in black; on fol. 2r it is on a 5-line staff in black; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: The offices of Archangel Michael and of St. Gall begin with 2-line initials in red and blue; the insider of the letters is decorated with an animal on a red and green ground surrounded by red and blue penwork and white dots; the outside of the letters is surrounded by red and blue penwork; 2-line initials of antiphons and responses alternate red and blue; the 2-line initial of the verse is in brown highlighted with red; the left margins of both versos are decorated with red and blue designs, which are topped by an animal head in red on fol. 1v; musical notation is in black on a 5-line staff in black; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Lessons for the Mass (from a Lectionary or Missal) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Lessons for the Mass (from a Lectionary or Missal) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the words "In illo tempore" begin with a 7- to 8-line initial "I" in blue with red penwork; the initials of the lessons are 1-line red or blue initials decorated with blue or red penwork; 1-line initials within lessons are in black highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation and accents are in the same ink as the text; there are symbols similar to neumes above some of the text, perhaps aids for reading aloud.

title: Flores Grammaticae (fragment).
note_text: Script: main text written in gothic script (littera textualis); the commentary is added in a contemporary or slightly later hand in littera cursiva currens, both marginally and interlinearly.

title: Flores Grammaticae (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials of each verse are in brown filled with red and are written with the text inside the single bounding line; there are frequent paragraph marks in red preceding the initials outside the bounding line; punctuated with the punctus; the commentary also has paragraph marks in red.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 3-line initials at the beginning of lessons alternate blue with red flourishes or red with not flourishes; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses are black, highlighted with red dots; punctuated with the punctus and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of rounded gothic script (littera textualis), a larger script for the lessons and prayers and a smaller script for chants.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials of prayers and lessons alternate red and blue; 1-line initials within lessons, of chants and the first letters following a 2-line initial are brown and yellow; rubrics written in a red cursive script; punctuated with the punctus; a contemporary hand has made corrections in black ink.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2- and 3-line initials at the beginning of lessons and prayers alternate blue decorated with red penwork and red with no flourishes (the blue is faded); 1-line initials beginning the second word of the lessons alternate red and blue; other 1-line initials are brown highlighted with red strokes and dots; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation added by a later hand.

title: On Virtues and Vices (fragment).
note_text: Script: The upper text is written in a gothic script (littera textualis currens); the lower text is written in Caroline minuscule.

title: On Virtues and Vices (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are in brown and are not set apart from the text; there is a space for a 2-line initial on fol. 1r, but it has not been added; punctuated with the punctus; authorities for specific passages in the upper text are written in the outer margins.

title: Buchlein der Ewigen Weisheit (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Buchlein der Ewigen Weisheit (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 3-line initials at the beginning of chapters are in red; 1-line initials are in black highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus and virgule.

title: Rituale (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Rituale (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials in red are surrounded by and filled with brown circles and flourishes; 1-line initials are in brown; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in rounded gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: The 4-line initial at the beginning of the office is blue and red with blue and red flourishes; 2-line initials at the beginning of responses alternate blue and red; 2-line initials at the beginning of verses are brown with brown and yellow flourishes; 1-line initials within verses are in brown and are highlighted with red; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; musical notation is on a four-line staff.

title: Bible, Matthew (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a minute gothic script (littera cursiva libraria).

title: Bible, Matthew (fragment).
note_text: Decoration:

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a hybrid gothic script (littera textualis with frequent but not consistent use of cursive forms of d, b, l, and t; s and f do not descend below the base line).

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials at the beginning of lessons are in red; other 1-line initials are in brown highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; liturgical directions are written in brown and are underlined in red; punctuated with the punctus and virgule.

title: Orationes Philippicae (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a round humanistic bookhand.

title: Orationes Philippicae (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are in brown square capitals; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials are in red; 1-line initials are in brown highlighted with red; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; the foliation is written in red in the upper center of the recto; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Lessons for the Mass (from a Lectionary or Missal) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Lessons for the Mass (from a Lectionary or Missal) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1- and 3-line initials at the beginning of lessons are in red; initials at the beginning of verses are in brown highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a hybrid gothic script mixing elements of littera bastarda and littera cursiva formata.

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: Historiated 7-line initial "O" on the recto in blue with white highlights filled by a depiction of the apostle Paul standing on a green field with a gold ground; Paul holds a book in his left hand and a sword in his right; the 2-line initial at the beginning of the antiphon is in red, surrounded by brown penwork; 1-line initials are in black; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Hymnal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Hymnal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2- to 12-line initials at the beginning of hymns are in red; only those that begin with the letter "I" are set apart from the text; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses are in red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Initial (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Initial (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: historiated initial "R"; the initial is blue with white highlights on a gold ground contained within a square green border; the inside of the letter depicts Christ rising from a coffin surrounded by three sleeping guards; musical notation in black on a 4-line staff of lead, yellow, lead, and red lines.

title: Initial (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Initial (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: large illuminated initial "D" or "O" in blue, pink, green, and red on a gold ground, with elongated marginal flourishes ending in gold balls outlined and decorated with black; musical notation in black on a 4-line staff in red; there is no punctuation.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the 4-line initial "U" is in blue and red; some of the sketched flourishes outside of the letter have been traced in red and filled with green; inside the letter a floral pattern has been sketched and partially completed; the 2-line initial "O" is red with sketched flourishes only partially completed and filled with green; rubrics in red in the same script as the text; quadrata notation is in black on a 4-line staff in red; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis), with a larger script for the prayers and a smaller script for the chants.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1- and 2-line initials alternate red and blue; rubrics are in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: There is a 7-line initial "E" on fol. 1v in pink with red and white highlights on a gold ground; green and blue vines with pink flowers extend from the initial into the lower margin and the forks in the vines were once filled with gold wedges; other 1- to 4-line initials are in red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis formata), with a larger script for the lessons and prayers and a smaller script for the chants.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: The 2-line initial beginning the Mass of Feria III is a blue uncial; the 8-line initial "I" beginning the lesson is red; 1-line initials are uncials in red or black highlighted with red; rubrics written in red; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; the foliation is written in red roman numerals in the center of the upper margin of the recto.

title: Index from a Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata) in red and black ink.

title: Index from a Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the 1-line initials at the beginning of each line are in red or in black highlighted with red; the feasts of Advent, the canon and prefaces of the Mass, the first Sunday after Easter, the beginning of the sanctorale, and all the items of the Commons are written in red; other important feast days such as Christmas, Epiphany, Easter, and Pentecost begin with a paragraph mark in red; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis), with a larger script for the lessons and prayers and a smaller script for the chants.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 6- to 7-line initials "I" at the beginning of lessons are in red; other 1-, 2-, and 3-line initials are in red; 1-line initials within lessons are in black highlighted with red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis formata) with a larger script for the lessons and prayers and a smaller script for the chants.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: there are spaces for initials and rubrics, but none have been added except for the lengthy rubric on fol. 2v; 1-line capitals within lessons are black; punctuated with the punctus, rarely; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; accents added by a later hand.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis formata), with a smaller script for the chants and a larger one for the prayers and lessons.

title: Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials at the beginning of Masses and lessons and 1-line initials at the beginning of chants and prayers alternate red and blue uncials; 1-line initials within the lessons are in brown highlighted with red; the rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Missale Bambergense (Johann Sensenschmidt) (fragment).
note_text: Script: printed in two sizes of gothic typeface; the larger is for the lessons and prayers and the smaller type is for the chants.

title: Missale Bambergense (Johann Sensenschmidt) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials at the beginning of Masses, prayers, and lessons and 1-line initials at the beginning of chants are in red and are adorned with balls; 1-line initials of verses and within lessons are in black; rubrics are printed in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus, the colon, and the punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic cursive script.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are written in brown; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Humanistic notarial script.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the document begins with a 7-line initial "I" in brown; 1-line initials within the text are in brown; punctuated with the punctus, the comma, and the punctus versus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Sequentiary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Sequentiary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials at the beginning of sequences are in red, decorated with blue penwork; 1-line initials at the beginning of verses alternate red and blue; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; musical notation in black on four-line staff in red.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Italian notarial script.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the document begins with a 6-line initial "I" in brown; 1-line initials are written in brown; punctuated with the punctus and the colon; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Italian notarial minuscule.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the document begins with a 7-line initial "I" in brown; 1-line initials within the text are in brown; punctuated with the colon; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a cursive gothic script (littera cursiva) in a hand similar to that of the scribe who wrote the document in MS 482.144.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the first word of the document ("Ich") is enlarged, with the initial "I" trailing down the margin of the entire text; there is no punctuation.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in cursive gothic script (littera cursiva), similar to that of the scribe who wrote the document in MS 482.143.

title: Legal Document (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the document begins with a flourished initial; there is no punctuation.

title: Noted Missal (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic script (littera textualis formata) without feet on the minims.

title: Noted Missal (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: one 9-line initial "P" on fol. 1r in varying shades of blue with foliate decoration on white filigree; in the loop of the letter a peacock in blue and grey with green and gold feathers stands underneath a red rose; the text on the recto is bordered on all four sides and in the center margin with a gold band filled with blue diamons alternating with circles filled with flowers; musical notation is in black on 4-line staves in red; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials in gold on a blue ground decorated with white filigree; initials filled with red and decorated with white filigree; 1-line initials are in black highlighted with yellow; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; the outer margin is modestly decorated with vine tendrils in black with green and gold leaves and blue, red, and pink flowers and berries.

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Book of Hours (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: two miniatures of mediocre quality, one for each saint; the miniature of St. Nicholas shows him in bishop's clothing, holding a staff and a book, and standing next to a tub with two children in it; St. Catharine is depicted as crowned, holding a book and a sword; on the floor behind her is the wheel upon which she was tortured; the antiphons and orations begin with a 2-line initial in gold on an alternating ground of blue with white filigree or red; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; rubrics written in red minuscule; upper, lower, and outer borders decorated with blue and gold vines, red vines with blue and red or gold and blue with gold flowers in the inner margin on the recto only.

title: Book of Hours (Litanies) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera fere bastarda).

title: Book of Hours (Litanies) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: each line begins with a 1-line initial "S" in gold on alternating grounds of red and blue; the names of the saints are written on the same line as "Or[a pros nobis]" but are separated from it by line fillers or alternating bands of red and blue decoraed with gold penwork; there is no punctuation.

title: Gradual (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Gradual (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 4-line historiated initial "D" in blue on a dark red ground bordered with gold; the initial, of workshop quality and badly rubbed and damaged by water, shows Christ standing on the shore with Andrew and Peter in a boat; the extant margins on the recto are decorated with blue and gold vines from which come pink, green, and gold flowers; rubrics written in red in a less formal script than the text; punctuated with the punctus; words and syllables are separated by horizontal strokes in red; the foliation is written in red in the center of the upper margin of the recto.

title: Initial (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: initial "N" in light pink decorated with white foliate patterns around the outer edge of the letter and white dots around the inner edge; the ends of the letter terminate in green and yellow; the letter is on a gold geometric ground that is outlined in black and filled with green, pink, and red leaves attached to a blue vine and with balls that are half white and half blue or green.

title: Initials (from a Psalter) (fragment).
note_text: Script: One letter "o" is preserved following the "H", written in gothic script in black ink.

title: Initials (from a Psalter) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: two 2-line initials "L" and "H" in blue decorated with foliate ornamentation outlined in brown and colored with green; the initials are for the beginning of Psalm verses.

title: Initials (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Initials (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 5-line initial "D" underneath which is a 2-line initial "U", 1-line initials "Q", "Q", "H", "Q", and "G", and a 2-line initial "U"; the initial "D" is in a dark red decorated with white penwork and on a gold ground; it is filled with blue and white vines in an s-shape that is attached to red flowers decorated with white penwork; the letters are attached by a vertical strip of gold and blue with both ends terminating in blue and red vines with blue, red, and gold flowers.

title: Initials (from a Psalter) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Initials (from a Psalter) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: four 3-line initials from the beginning of Psalms; the first two initials are blue uncials on a square pink ground bordered in greeen; the second two are pink uncials on a square blue ground bordered in green; all four initials are filled with gold in which there are pink, green, or blue vines with white, yellow, or pink flowers; these initials are very similar in design, decoration, and size to the initials in MSS 483.8-9; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Missal (use of Sarum) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Missal (use of Sarum) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: there are three 2-line initials in blue with red penwork trailing up and down the entire margin or the column; 1-line initials are in brown; rubrics are written in red; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2- and 3-line initials alternate red with blue penwork and blue with red penwork; rubrics written in red minuscule; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus.

title: Noted Breviary, use of Sarum (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Noted Breviary, use of Sarum (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials are in blue with red penwork or in black with black penwork; 1-line initials are in black; rubrics are written in red minuscule; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; musical notation is in black on 4-line staves in red.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal, rounded Italian gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the 6-line initial "M" at the beginning of the Psalm is in gold, on a square ground of blue decorated with white filigree; the inside of the initial depicts a good-quality image of David kneeling against a mauve background and looking up to the hand of god; 1-line initials at the beginning of Psalm verses and antiphons alternate in red and blue uncials; rubrics written in red capitals; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; musical notation is in black on 4-line staves in red.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal, rounded Italian gothic script (littera textualis formata).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the 7-line initial "D" at the beginning of the Psalm is in light tan and gold on a square ground in blue with white filigree; the inside of the initial contains a miniature that is badly rubbed, depicting Christ holding a book on a mauve ground; the first line of the Psalm is written in 1-line white capitals on a rectangular red ground; guide letters for the artist are in the margin in red; 1-line initials are black capitals highlighted with red; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; musical notation is in black on 4-line staves in red.

title: Super infortiato et Digesto Novo (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a cramped and inelegant gothic script (scripture notularis).

title: Super infortiato et Digesto Novo (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: two 2-line initials alternating red and blue decorated with red penwork; rubrics written in red gothic cursive; the lemmata are marked with alternating red and blue paragraph marks, and some are underlined in brown; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Book of Hours (Office of the Dead) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic script (littera textualis formata), with a larger script for the canticle and Psalm and a smaller script for the chants.

title: Book of Hours (Office of the Dead) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the 2-line initial at the beginning of the Psalm and the 1-line initials at the beginning of Psalm verses are in gold on a ground that alternates between red with blue penwork and blue with white penwork; the interior of letters on the red ground are filled with blue and white penwork, and the interiors of those on blue ground are filled with red and blue penwork; 1-line initials at the beginning of chants are in brown; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated rarely with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Commentaries on the Psalms (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule.

title: Commentaries on the Psalms (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2- and 3-line initials at the beginning of each commentary are in red uncials; they are frequently decorated with balls or cross-hatching; 1-line initials are in brown uncials with occasional use of rustic capital forms; the first several words of each commentary are written in brown rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus versus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; accents were added by a later hand.

title: South German Homiliary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule, which Bischoff (on the basis of his inspection of other leaves of the same manuscript) dated to the second quarter of the ninth century.

title: South German Homiliary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the homily on fol. 1v begins with a 3-line initial "T" outlined in orange and filled and surrounded with brown; 1-line initials are in orange uncials and are set apart from the text between the double vertical bounding lines; punctuated with the punctus and punctus versus.

title: Sermons (Alan of Farfa, Homiliary?) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule, which Bischoff has dated to the first third of the ninth century.

title: Sermons (Alan of Farfa, Homiliary?) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the homily begins with a 7-line decorated initial "F" outlined in brown and filled with orange, dark orange, ochre, and olive green; 1-line initials in brown uncials; rubric written in red uncials; punctuated with the punctus and punctus versus; a leaf has been drawn in red in the space between the columns on the verso.

title: Ars Laureshamensis, Expositio in Donatum maiorem (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule.

title: Ars Laureshamensis, Expositio in Donatum maiorem (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are brown rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus and punctus interrogativus; double quotation marks are within the text.

title: De syllogismo categorico, De differentiis topicis (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a highly abbreviated, late Caroline script.

title: De syllogismo categorico, De differentiis topicis (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2- and 3-line initials at the beginning of each section are red; 1-line initials are brown rustic capitals; the explicit is written in brown rustic capitals with some use of uncial and minuscule forms; there are nine diagrams, one outlined in red; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule.

title: Sacramentary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initials are red rustic capitals with single round "D"; 1-line initials are brown uncials; rubrics written in red rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus and punctus versus; accents in the same ink as the text.

title: Historiae Alexandri Magni (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in rounded gothic bookhand (gothico-humanistica).

title: Historiae Alexandri Magni (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are brown capitals; there are brief notes on the text written in the margin in a cursive humanistic script of the fifteenth century; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Bible, Luke (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule.

title: Bible, Luke (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1- and 2-line initials alternate in red and green uncials; 1-line initials are brown uncials; the running title "Secundum" / "Lucam" is written in brown rustic capitals in the upper margin; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, punctus versus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; canon table numbers are written in the left marins in red roman numerals.

title: Homiliae xl in evangelia (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Homiliae xl in evangelia (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: At the beginning of Homily 4 (fol. 2r) there is a 3-line initial "C" sketched, but not completed, in brown ink with foliate decoration; it may be a later addition; 1-line initials are brown uncials; the rubrics for Homily 4 and its lesson are written in red minuscule mixed with uncial forms, with red line-filler; there are no initials or rubrics for the beginning of each lesson; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text; accents were added by a later hand; on fol. 2v there are three interlinear Latin glosses in a fifteenth-century hand; other fifteenth-century hands have added marginal notations and figures of heads on fols. 7v-8r.

title: Passio S. Felicitatis (from a Passionary?) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in an inelegant Caroline minuscule.

title: Passio S. Felicitatis (from a Passionary?) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are brown rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus versus.

title: Homiliae xl in evangelia (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Homiliae xl in evangelia (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 1-line initials are brown uncials; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation in the same ink as the text.

title: Homilies (Haimo of Halberstadt?) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule.

title: Homilies (Haimo of Halberstadt?) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: on fol. 1v there is a very fine 3/4-page decorated initial "I" in red and yellow on a purple, blue, and orange ground, with vine-stem decoration lightly washed with yellow; 1-line initials are either in red rustic capitals or brown rustic capitals highlighted with red; rubrics are written in a mixture of red minuscule and rustic capitals; punctuated with the punctus and punctus elevatus; double quotation marks are within the text; accents are in the same ink as the text.

title: Noted Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of Caroline minuscule, with a larger script for the lessons and hymn and a smaller script for the antiphons and responses.

title: Noted Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: on fol. 1v there are decorated initials "I" (7-line) and "F" (8-line), outlined in orange and colored with green and yellow ; 1- and 2-line initials are orange uncials; 1-line initials within the hymn are a mixture of orange uncials and rustic capitals; rubrics are written in orange minuscule; interlinear neumes in the St. Gall style; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; accents and diacritical marks over double "i" by later hands.

title: Homiliae (Expositios super Mattheum) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Homiliae (Expositios super Mattheum) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 2-line initial "E" is a red uncial highlighted with yellow; 1-line initials are a mixture of brown uncials, rustic capitals, and enlarged minuscule forms, usually filled with yellow; the rubric is written in red minuscule; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus, some of the last altered from the punctus by a corrector; hyphenation in the same ink as the text.

title: Passionary (Passio S. Cassiani) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Beneventan script.

title: Passionary (Passio S. Cassiani) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the Prudentius life is written in poetic stanzas; six-line decorated initial is outlined in brown; 1-line initials are brown uncials; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus versus.

title: Homiliary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in Caroline minuscule.

title: Homiliary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 7-line initial "L" is in red, the horizontal stroke decorated with two round balls; 1-line initials are brown uncials; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text, but in a larger module; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Homiliary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in late Caroline minuscule.

title: Homiliary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: on fol. 1r there is a fine 7-line decorated initial "E" in yellow filled with red geometric penwork on a ground of blue, green, and dark red, with four vine stems originating from the lower bar of the "E"; a guide letter appears in the margin opposite the decorated initial; 1-line initials are black uncials; rubrics written in red uncials; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation and accents were added by a later hand.

title: Bible, Genesis (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in two sizes of gothic bookhand (littera textualis).

title: Bible, Genesis (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the preface on fol. 2r begins with a 10-line decorated initial "D" in red interlace on a green geometric ground with a blue ground for the central portion of the vine stem; the text of Genesis begins with a half-page decorated initial "I" in the same style; 1-line initials in the prefatory material are occasionally red; line fillers are in red; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text; accents added by a later hand; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Bible, Sirach (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a late Caroline minuscule.

title: Bible, Sirach (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: 3- to 7-line initials are red uncials; 1-line initials are black uncials; chapter headings are written in red minuscule in a larger module; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, punctus versus, and punctus interrogativus; hyphenation added by a later hand.

title: Gradual (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic bookhand (littera textualis formata), with musical notation in black on a four-line staff in red.

title: Gradual (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the parchment and writing appear to be from the sixteenth century, but the decoration was added in modern times; there is a 2-line initial "U" in blue, green, and purple on a gold ground and containing the figure of an angel striking a tambourine; foliage decorations in the same colors as the initial extend from the initial into the left margin; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic bookhand (littera textualis formata).

title: Breviary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: the 2-line initial "S" at the beginning of the hymn is in olive-green, green, and red with white filigree and is filled with purple, blue, and red foliage decorated with white filigree; the initial is on a gold ground outlined in black and is surrounded by green, blue, and orange foliage that extends into the margin with gold balls; 1-line initials alternate blue and red; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus, punctus elevatus, and punctus flexus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic bookhand (littera textualis formata).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: musical notation in black on a five-line staff in red; on the recto there is a 2-line initial "C" in red and blue on a rectangular ground of red and blue penwork; the 2-line initial "E" on the verso and the 1-line initials are black; rubrics are written in red in the same script as the text, but in a smaller module; punctuated with the punctus; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Gradual (or Missal) (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic bookhand (littera textualis formata).

title: Gradual (or Missal) (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: musical notation in brown on 4-line staves in red; 1-line initials alternate red with brown penwork and blue with red penwork; the 1-line initial at the beginning of the rubric is a blue capital with red penwork, and the rubric is written in in a smaller version of the text script; words and syllables are divided by red horizontal strokes; punctuated with the punctus.

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a formal gothic bookhand (littera textualis formata).

title: Antiphonary (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: on the recto there is a 4-line initial "C", in red and blue on a ground outlined in purple and decorated with purple foliage on red cross-hatching; 1-line initials at the beginning of the hymn and the psalm are red; rubrics written in red in the same script as the text; punctuated with the punctus and the comma; hyphenation is in the same ink as the text.

title: Gradual (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in gothic script (littera textualis).

title: Gradual (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: one 4-line initial "I", the body of which is divided into three columns of blue, blue-grey, and light brown, each column decorated with a different pattern of white filigree; the first letter of the rubric is a blue uncial with red penwork, and the rest of the rubric is written in red; punctuated with the punctus; musical notation is in black on 4-line staves in red.

title: The robin book : watching the robins / copyright by H. Boylston Dummer : Rockport, Mass., [circa 1925].
note_text: Signed in by the creator on first and last pages.

title: The robin book : watching the robins / copyright by H. Boylston Dummer : Rockport, Mass., [circa 1925].
note_text: Bound with black string and staples.

title: The robin book : watching the robins / copyright by H. Boylston Dummer : Rockport, Mass., [circa 1925].
note_text: Some manuscript corrections in pencil.

title: A catalogue of the capital collection of coins and medals, in the highest preservation, and beautiful painted glass, of John Ives, Esq., F.R.S. F.S.A. ... [1777].
note_text: Bound with: A catalogue of the entire and valuable library of John Ives, Jun. [London] : Catalogues to be had of the following booksellers; Mr. Dodsley's ... Mr. Robson's ... Mr. Walter's ... Mr. Edwards's ... Mr. Sewel's ... Mr. Owen's ... and at the place of sale, [1777].

title: "Glossa Ordinaria" on the Decretals of Gregory IX (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a heavily abbreviated gothic script.

title: "Glossa Ordinaria" on the Decretals of Gregory IX (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: running heads, initials, and rubrics in red; some contemporary marginal commentary.

title: "Glossa Ordinaria" on the Decretals of Gregory IX (fragment).
note_text: These fragments, which appear to be from the same manuscript, are contained in Zi +156 (Bernhard von Breydenbach, Prefatio in opus transmarine...), in which the fragments are used as front and back endpapers.

title: Bible, Matthew (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: initials in red.

title: Bible, Matthew (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in an unidentified script.

title: Bible, Matthew (fragment).
note_text: Contained in Zi +237 (Dionysius de Burgo Sancti Sepulcri, Commentarii in Valerium Maximum), in which the fragment has been used as a spine support.

title: Liturgical book (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a gothic script.

title: Liturgical book (fragment).
note_text: Decoration: square notation on a four-line red stave.

title: Liturgical book (fragment).
note_text: This fragment is contained in Zi +318 (Johannes Auerbach, Summa de auditione...), around which the fragment is used as a wrapper.

title: Doctrinale Puerorum (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in a late bâtarde script with heavy marginal annotations.

title: Doctrinale Puerorum (fragment).
note_text: These fragments, which appear to be from the same manuscript, are contained in Zi +347 (Johannes Nider, Praeceptorium divinae legis), in which they are used as front and back spine supports.

title: [unidentified text] (fragment).
note_text: Script: written in an unidentified script.

title: [unidentified text] (fragment).
note_text: These fragments, which appear to be from the same manuscript, are contained in Zi +426 (Corona Beatae Mariae Virginis), in which they are used as front and back spine guards (uppermost of series of four).

title: [unidentified text] (fragment).

title: Grammatical Preface and Scala Ecclesiastica.
note_text: Bound together with: Abu Ishaq ibn al-Assal, Scala Rimata. John of Samannud's Grammatical Preface and Scala Ecclesiastica were originally written in the 13th century. All three texts preserved are Coptic grammatical works, presumably for continuation of the language, which was waning in popularity. According to internal Coptic numeration, first nine pages are missing. Numbered folios = 9-123. Contains chapter divisions (Cpt. = kephaleon). Some sections are alphabetically arranged. Many pages still bound in sections. Severe worming and heavy damage to some pages. Significant staining throughout. Some Arabic marginalia. Some letters excised.

note_text: Colophon: "Wa-kāna al-farāgh min kitābat hādhihi al-risālah yawm al-Ithnayn al-mubārak min shahr Ramaḍān al-mubārak alladhī huwa min shuhūr sanat 1215. Wa-al-ḥamd lillāh Rabb al-ʻĀlamīn wa-ḥasbunā Allāh wa-niʻma al-wakīl. Wa-lā ḥawla wa-lā qūwata illā billāh al-ʻalī al-ʻaẓīm. Wa-ṣallá Allāh ʻalá Sayyidinā Muḥammad al-nabī al-ummī wa-ʻalá ālihi wa-ṣaḥbihi wa-sallam. Muḥammad Aḥmad ʻAlī ʻĪsá al-Bukhārī ghafara Allāh la-hu wa-li-uṣūl uṣūlih wa-furūʻ furūʻih."

title: 880-02 Maṭlaʻ al-nayyirayn fīmā yataʻallaqu bi-al-qudratayn : manuscript / Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad al-Sunbāwī al-Amīr al-Kabīr al-Mālikī.
note_text: Translation of the colophon: "The writing of this treatise was concluded on blessed Monday in blessed Ramaḍān, 1215. Praise be to God the Lord of the Universe. God suffices us. He is the best advocate. There is no power nor might except in God the most high and the most powerful. May God pray on our master Muḥammad the illiterate prophet and on his family and companions and grant them peace. [Copied by] Muḥammad Aḥmad ʻAlī ʻĪsá al-Bukhārī. May God forgive him and the origins of his origins and the branches of his branches."

note_text: Translation of the colophon: "This is the end of the book. Praise be to God in all matters. God suffices us. He is the best advocate. May God pray on our Master Muḥammad, the seal of the prophets and the leader of the messengers, and on his family and companions and grant them peace as long as He is remembered by those who remember and by those who are negligent, a continuous and permanent prayer until judgement day. Praise be to God the Lord of the Universe."

title: [Psalter and prayers].
note_text: Bound in plain wooden boards; four chain stitches, in leather case consisting of two parts, with carrying strap. Ff. 3r-130r: Psalter and Praises of Mary. Contains depictions of David and Gabriel(?). Some small holes in ms. Some marginal prayers. Some purple ink and pencil marginalia. Ethiopic writing and grafitti in the flyleaves. Includes printed page of Pss 3 and 4. Includes 1930 letters (copies) from Richard Gottheil of Columbia University regarding the ms.

title: [Psalter and prayers].
note_text: Ff. 1r-1v (written upside down): Concluding prayer to be recited after the Praises of Mary, including appeals to Mary to intercede for members of the family of the owner of the book, Qaṣalā Giyoregis, in an untrained hand. Otherwise in the hand of Takela Giyoregis in red and black with the exception of ownership notes and pen trials. In Geʼez.

title: [Psalter and prayers].
note_text: F. 130v: Colophon begins with a condemnation on anyone who steals or erases anything in the book. The book was written by Takela Giyoregis in 1917 EC, Tahsas 1.

title: [Psalter and prayers].
note_text: F. 132v: Pen trials, based on the opening prayer of the Psalter.

Wa-qad iʻtaná bi-shaʼnihā jamāʻah min al-shurrāḥ ajalluhum al-Shaykh Raḍī al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥasan al-Astarābādī. Wa-mā atá bi-hi sharḥ jāmiʻ awwaluhu 'Ammā baʻda ḥamd Allāh taʻālá ʻalá tawālī niʻamih' ilá ākhirihi, kadhā fī Kashf al-Ẓunūn bi-al-tamām wa-al-kamāl wa-al-ḥamdu lillāh ʻalá kull ḥāl."

title: 880-02 Sharḥ Shāfiyat Ibn al-Ḥājib : manuscript / Raḍī al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥasan al-Astarābādhī.
note_text: On folio 1a an endowment statement: "Waqafa wa-aḥbasa hādhā al-kitāb al-faqīr ilá Allāh taʻālá Muḥammad al-Bahī ibn al-Shaykh Muṣṭafá al-Ḥuwayḥī thumma al-Ṭandatānī ʻalá ṭalabat al-ʻilm wa-jaʻala al-naẓar li-nafsihi thumma li-man yaṣluḥu min awlādihi waqfan ṣaḥīḥan sharʻīyan lā yubāʻu wa-lā yurhanu wa-lā yubaddalu, fa-man baddalahu baʻdamā samiʻahu fa-innamā ithmuhu ʻalá alladhīna yubaddilūnahu. Taḥrīran fī 3 Rajab sanat 1294 [14 July, 1877]."

title: 880-02 Sharḥ Shāfiyat Ibn al-Ḥājib : manuscript / Raḍī al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥasan al-Astarābādhī.
note_text: Colophon: "al-Ḥamdu lillāh mulhim al-ṣawāb wa-al-sadād al-muwaffiq li-man arāda al-wuṣūl ilá al-murād wa-al-ṣalāh wa-al-salām ʻalá al-Nabī al-ʻAdnān wa-ʻalá ālihi wa-ṣaḥbihi al-fāyizīn min Allāh bi-al-jinān. Wa-baʻd fa-yaqūlu al-rājī ʻafwa Rabbihi al-ʻālim Muḥammad ʻAlī al-mulaqqab bi-Abī Sālim: Tamma bi-ḥamd Allāh ṣāḥib al-niʻam al-kāfiyah naskhī sharḥ al-ʻAllāmah Raḍī al-Dīn ʻalá al-Shāfiyah fa-jāʼa bi-ḥamd Allāh muḥarraran muwaḍḍaḥan wa-munaqqaḥan muhadhdhaban muṣaḥḥaḥan wa-kāna dhālika al-tamām wa-al-ḥuṣūl wa-al-khitām muwāfiqan li-thamāniyah wa-ʻishrīn yawman khalat min shahr Jumād al-Awwal alladhī huwa min shuhūr iḥdá wa-tisʻīn wa-miʼatayn wa-alf min Hijrat man khalaqahu Allāh ʻalá akmal waṣf ṣallá Allāh ʻlayhi wa-ʻalá ālihi wa-kull nāsij ʻalá minwālih mā tawālá al-jadīdān wa-ṭalaʻa al-Zibriqān. Āmīn, bi-jāh al-Amīn. M."

title: 880-02 Sharḥ Shāfiyat Ibn al-Ḥājib : manuscript / Raḍī al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥasan al-Astarābādhī.
note_text: Translation of the colophon: "Praise be to God who inspires what is true and correct and grants success to whoever endeavors to reach his goal. May prayer and peace be upon the ʻAdnanite Prophet, his family and his companions to whom God granted Paradise. Thereafter, Muḥammad ʻAlī, nicknamed Abū Sālim, who hopes for the forgiveness from his All Knowing Lord, says: Concluded is -- by the praise of God the bestower of the abundant graces -- the copying of the commentary of the learned scholar Raḍī al-Dīn on al-Shāfiyah. It was edited, explained, revised, elucidated and corrected. This was accomplished on the 28th of Jumād al-Awwal, of the year 1291 of the Hijrah of the One whom God created with perfect character, may God pray upon him and upon his family and those who follow him, as long as night and day alternate and the Moon shines, by the intercession of the the Faithful One. Amen."

note_text: On folio 1a: "Kitāb al-Nafḥah al-miskīyah wa-al-tuḥfah al-Makkīyah taʼlīf al-Shaykh al-Imām al-ʻālim al-ʻallāmah Shaykh al-Islām wa-al-Muslimīn faṣīḥ ʻaṣrih wa-farīd dahrih al-Shaykh Jalāl al-Dīn al-Suyūṭī nafaʻanā Allāh taʻālá bi-barakātih wa-aʻāda ʻalaynā wa-al-Muslimīn min ṣāliḥ daʻawātih fī al-dīn wa-al-dunyā."

title: 880-02 al-Nafḥah al-miskīyah wa-al-tuḥfah al-Makkīyah : manuscript / Jalāl al-Dīn al-Suyūṭī.
note_text: Colophon: "... wa-dhālika fī shahr Allāh Rajab, fī yawm al-Arbiʻāʼ al-thānī wa-al-ʻishrīn minhu sanat tisʻ wa-sittīn wa-thamānimiʼah. Tammat bi-ḥamd Allāh taʻālá wa-ʻawnih wa-ḥusn tawfīqih. Wa-al-ḥamdu lillāh waḥdah wa-kafá wa-salāmun ʻalá ʻibādihi alldhīna iṣṭafá wa-ṣallá Allāh [ʻalá] Sayyidinā Muḥammad al-nabī al-muṣṭafá."

title: 880-02 al-Nafḥah al-miskīyah wa-al-tuḥfah al-Makkīyah : manuscript / Jalāl al-Dīn al-Suyūṭī.
note_text: Translation of the colophon: "It is concluded by the praise of God and his abundant benevolence, on Wednesday, 22 of God's month Rajab, 869 [29 March, 1465]. Praise be to God alone and that is sufficient. Peace be on His servants whom He had chosen. May God pray on our master Muḥammad the chosen prophet."

title: 880-02 Nuzʹhat al-arwāḥ fī baʻḍ awṣāf al-Jannah dār al-afrāḥ : manuscript / Yūsuf ibn Saʻīd al-Ṣafatī al-Mālikī al-Azʹharī.
note_text: Colophon: "Tammat hādhihi al-risālah yawm al-Jumʻah al-mubārakah khamsah fī shahr Jumād al-Awwal sanat alf wa-miʼatayn thamāniyah wa-sabʻīn min al-Hijr [al-Hijrah] al-Nabwah [al-Nabawīyah] ʻalá yad kātibihā al-faqīr Muḥammad al-Asyūṭī al-Mālikī ghafara Allāh la-hu waliday [wa-li-wālidayhi] wa-mashāyikhihi wa-al-Muslimīn wa-asʼalu Allāh an yanfaʻa bi-hā kamā nafaʻa bi-uṣūlihā wa-an yajʻalahā khāliṣatan li-wajhihi al-karīm wa-sababan lil-fawz bi-ruʼyatihi fī janāt al-naʻīm. Wa-al-ḥamdu lillāh Rabb al-ʻĀlamīn. Wa-ṣallá Allāh ʻalá Sayyidinā Muḥammad wa-ʻalá ālihi wa-ṣaḥbihi ajmaʻīn. Āmīn."

title: 880-02 Nuzʹhat al-arwāḥ fī baʻḍ awṣāf al-Jannah dār al-afrāḥ : manuscript / Yūsuf ibn Saʻīd al-Ṣafatī al-Mālikī al-Azʹharī.
note_text: Translation of the colophon: "This treatise ended on blessed Friday, 5 Jumād al-Awwal, 1278 of the Hijrah of the Prophet [8 November, 1861] by its poor copyist, Muḥammad al-Asyūṭī al-Mālikī. May God forgive him and his parents, his teachers and all Muslims. I beseech God to make it beneficial as He made beneficial its origins; that God may be please with me and a reason to enable me to see Him in the Paradise of Bliss. Praise be to God the Lord of the Universe. May God pray on our Master Muḥammad and on his family and all his companions. Amen."

Ṣallá Allāh ʻalá Sayyidinā Muḥammad wa-ʻalá ālihi wa-ṣaḥbihi wa-sallama taslīman kathīran Wa-al-ḥamdu lillāh Rabb al-ʻĀlamīn."

title: [Psalter, Song of Songs, and hymn].
note_text: Wood covers, four chain stitches, leather Oriental binding, fine cloth visible between the paste downs. German typescript of Holmes' notes glued to the flyleaf -- Holmes mentions that the MS contains a Psalter, Song of Songs, and a praise of Mary, and hypothesizes regarding the purpose of the outer calf-skin capsule. Sparse marginalia and scribal corrections. Some holes and tears in MS are stitched back together. Minor worming on the back cover.

title: [Psalter, Song of Songs, and hymn].

Class of 1872. 1920 [date of donation?]; F. 2 contains a report in German of the contents and date of the book, in which the writer makes a case for the 17th century. However, the Psalter is clearly written by a hand of the late-nineteenth or early-twentieth century; Blank: Ff. 2v–4v, 145r–148v; Word for God is rubricated throughout.

title: [Psalter, with Psalms of the Saint Mary, Blessed Virgin, with Biblical Canticles, Song of Songs, and Gate of Light].
note_text: F. ii v, note of provenance: "This Psalter was one of the books found in Magdala when that place was taken by Sir Robert Napier, afterwards Lord Napier of Magdala, in 1868. The collection had been formed by [King] Theodore with the intention of founding a large Library. These books were carried off by our people, and partly given to Abyssinian churches on the march back to Zayla [?], and a number were brought back to England for our own and for foreign libraries. When nearing Zoula on the return march, M. Munzinger, who had charge of the books, found that he had a few to spare, and among them was this Psalter, which he gave to me. -- William Simpson, 2nd April, 1881."; F. 1r: note in the upper margin: ዳዊት ዘ ቅዱስ መድኃኔ ዓለም (this is the statement that the Psalter belonged to the Great Library to be formed at Magdala by Theodore -- W. Simpson); Fine cloth is visible between the paste downs of the front and back cover; The Qalu counting employs the number 9, and does not include the strophes of the Virgin Mary; Blank: ff. iii r, 209v.

title: Miniature of Benedictine nun kneeling before Christ.
note_text: Decoration: an example of the simple illustration style known as "nonnenarbeiten," which are devotional images produced by medieval nuns for personal use. The nun and Christ are placed in a grassy field comprised of penstrokes covered with a green wash. Details like Christ's wounds are conveyed through penstrokes as well. The instruments of the Passion are individually colored with wash: red and black for the cock, orange for the sponge, and orange for parts of the spear. An alternating blue and orange wash has been used to decorate the border of the miniature.

The document ends with: "... thumma ʻuriḍa dhālik ʻalá Ḥaḍrat Mawlānā Afandī, al-mushār ilayhi, fa-lammā an aḥāṭa ʻilmuhu al-karīm bi-dhālik, amara bi-kitābatihi wa-qaydihi bi-al-sijill al-maḥfūẓ ḍabṭan lil-wāqiʻ. Wa-taḥarrara dhālik bi-dūn rasm, bināʼan ʻalá al-khiṭābayn al-wāridayn li-hādhihi al-Maḥkamah min Naẓārat al-Ḥaqqānīyah, al-muʼarrakh aḥaduhumā fī rābiʻ ʻashar Rabīʻ Ākhir, sanat arbaʻ wa-thalāthmiʼah wa-alf [10 January 1887], al-muqayyid bi-nimrah arbaʻah ʻumūm, wa-al-thānī muʼarrakh fī tāsiʻ shahr Shaʻbān, sanat tārīkhihi [3 May, 1887], muqayyid bi-nimrah ithnayn wa-miʼah taḥrīran, fī tārīkhayn, awwaluhumā yawm ṣudūr al-isqāṭ al-madhkūr wa-al-ishhād bi-hi wa-al-tawāfuq ʻalá al-shurūṭ al-marqūmah, wa-huwa sādis shahr al-Qaʻdah, wa-thānīhumā yawm ṣudūr al-iqrār bi-al-qismah al-madhkūrah wa-al-ishhād bi-hi, wa-huwa ʻāshir shahr al-Qaʻdah al-madhkūr, sanat arbaʻ [corrected to sitt] wa-thalāthmiʼah wa-alf. ʻAlī al-Khaṭīb. Quyyidat bi-Sijill al-Mubāyaʻāt, nimrah 34, juzʼ 18, ʻadad 29. [two signatures]."
